        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "&amp;quot;A Program to Provide 90 Percent Assistance in Planting Material of Horticultural Fruit Crops&amp;quot; introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to support farmers by providing 90% subsidy on the cost of planting materials like grafted/tissue culture saplings and seedlings for various fruit crops.\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- Farmers receive up to 90% financial assistance on the cost of planting materials.\n> **Pre-fixed assistance rates per hectare for different crops:**\n\n\n<br>\n\nFruit Assistance Mango₹32,000/haSapota (Chiku)₹22,000/haPomegranate₹20,000/haGuava₹16,650/haAonla (Indian Gooseberry)₹5,560/haMandarin / Orange₹5,560/haBer₹2,780/haCoconut₹13,000/ha<br>\n\n> **Note:**\n\n\n- Only saplings costing up to ₹250/- per unit are eligible for subsidy.\n- **For fruit crops and cuttings:** Planting material will have to be purchased from nurseries accredited by NHB/Agricultural University/Horticulture Department.- **For coconut crops:** seedlings prepared from seeds will have to be purchased from nurseries accredited by NHB/Agricultural University/Horticulture Department.-  **For tissue culture:** Planting material (planting) will have to be purchased from tissue labs approved/accredited by DBT, GNFC, GSFC, Tissue Labs of Agricultural University, Government Public Institutions like\n",
        "briefDescription": "This scheme offers 90% financial assistance to farmers for purchasing planting materials of fruit crops to promote horticulture.\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
